<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>{# file login_ONIONBM.thtml #}
{# a template file for libOnion's template system #}
<head>
<title>Login to Bismon</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Login to Bismon</h1>
  <p><b><tt>Bismon</tt> stores <b>persistently</b> some <i>personal
    data</i> about you</b>, such as your username, internalid, email
    addresses. That data (as all of <tt>Bismon</tt>'s persistent
    state) might be shared or published thru
    e.g. <a href='http://git-scm.com/'>git</a> or other means. Do not
    login if you disagree.</p>
  <form action="_login" method="post">
    <input type='hidden' name='origpath' value='{{origpath}}'/>
    <b>user:</b> <input type='text' name='user'/><br/>
    <b>password:</b><input type='password' name='password'/><br/>
    <b>Connect:</b> <input type='submit' name='login' value='loginv'/> &nbsp;
    <b>Forgotten password:</b> <input type='submit' name='forgot' value='forgotv'>/> &nbsp;
  </form>
  <p>If you login, you have agreed for
  our <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_cookie'>web
  cookie</a>, and for the <tt>Bismon</tt> server to keep some personal
  data about you, and this session.</p>
</html>
